{"questionId":"21480","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>An ant is walking along the edges of a wire frame in the shape of a triangular prism.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/75246fd55eae20bdb5c10cfe47faf26e9dd3f3a7.png\"></p>\n<p>The vertices and edges of this frame can be represented by the graph below.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/ad1d3cef9ff82b72835c8238848fe6e201315c94.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the number of ways that the ant can start at the vertex <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math>, and walk along exactly&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn></math> edges to return to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>calculating&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">M</mi><mn>6</mn></msup></math>&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>143</mn></math>&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21480","referenceCode":"21M.1.AHL.TZ1.16b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the number of ways that the ant can start at the vertex A, and walk along exactly 6 edges to return to A.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.15—Adjacency matrices and tables"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}